.bond-container {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  margin: 20px;
  padding: 20px;
  border: 1px solid #ccc;
  background-color: #f9f9f9;
  border-radius: 20px; /* Adjust border radius for rounded corners */
}

/* Styles for the bond boxes */
.bond-box {
  flex: 0 0 calc(50% - 20px); /* Two boxes per row */
  padding: 10px;
  border: 1px solid #ddd;
  background-color: #fff;
  border-radius: 10px; /* Adjust border radius for rounded corners */
  margin: 10px; /* Add some space between the boxes */
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

/* ... other styles ... */
In this example, I've added border-radius: 20px; to the .bond-container class to make the bond containers more rounded, and I've kept border-radius: 10px; for the .bond-box class to maintain the rounded corners for the boxes.

Feel free to adjust the values of border-radius and other styles to achieve the desired appearance.





